WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:04.403
Dre:<i> Keeping a large family</i>
<i>together has its challenges,</i>

00:04.405 --> 00:05.571
<i>And lately, it seems like</i>

00:05.573 --> 00:07.239
<i>Everybody's doing</i>
<i>their own thing.</i>

00:07.241 --> 00:09.575
Ha-ha!
Hey, game night!

00:09.577 --> 00:11.110
I got cranium and jenga.

00:15.115 --> 00:17.316
I also have bananagrams.

00:19.452 --> 00:22.421
<i>Closed doors were not an option</i>
<i>when I was growing up.</i>

00:22.423 --> 00:25.057
[ drill whirs ]

00:25.059 --> 00:27.192
I'll put that back
when you move out.

00:27.194 --> 00:28.627
But then
I won't need it.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.629
Keep talking.
I'll take this whole room apart.

00:30.631 --> 00:33.132
[ drill whirs ]

00:33.134 --> 00:35.401
<i>When I was growing up,</i>
<i>you weren't allowed</i>

00:35.403 --> 00:37.503
<i>To separate yourself</i>
<i>from your family,</i>

00:37.505 --> 00:39.104
<i>Which is why I try to find ways</i>

00:39.106 --> 00:41.173
<i>To remind my kids</i>
<i>that they're a part</i>

00:41.175 --> 00:44.043
<i>Of something greater</i>
<i>than themselves.</i>

00:44.045 --> 00:46.779
Check this out.
Look what I got today.

00:46.781 --> 00:49.782
Oh, those are so cute.
Yeah, right?

00:49.784 --> 00:52.217
The kids
are gonna hate them.
But -- maybe.

00:52.219 --> 00:55.054
But they will
hate them together.

00:55.056 --> 00:56.422
Hey, hey,
slow your roll.

00:56.424 --> 00:57.589
I need to talk
to you two.

00:57.591 --> 01:00.125
Look, I want us
to start operating

01:00.127 --> 01:05.097
Spending more time together,
appreciating each other.

01:05.099 --> 01:06.832
Dad, are you dying?

01:06.834 --> 01:09.368
No, fool.

01:09.370 --> 01:11.103
Look, we're all going
to support jack

01:11.105 --> 01:12.504
At his baseball game,

01:12.506 --> 01:14.573
And we're all
going to wear these t-shirts

01:14.575 --> 01:15.607
To show family unity.

01:15.609 --> 01:17.709
Oh, that sounds great.

01:17.711 --> 01:20.746
Except I'm not wearing the shirt
or going to the game.

01:20.748 --> 01:22.114
Okay.

01:22.116 --> 01:23.615
What I have to say
to that

01:23.617 --> 01:26.452
Is wear the shirt
or be grounded.

01:26.454 --> 01:29.788
Can we take a minute
to huddle?

01:29.790 --> 01:35.094
What I have to say to that
is wear the shirt or eat.

01:37.230 --> 01:44.803
We're still gonna need
that minute.

01:44.805 --> 01:46.672
Man:<i> 2-1...</i>

01:46.674 --> 01:48.373
Rainbow: Okay, so when
it's your turn next,

01:48.375 --> 01:50.275
You focus, jack, okay?

01:50.277 --> 01:51.376
Focus, j.J.

01:51.378 --> 01:53.712
I should've eaten
this shirt.

01:53.714 --> 01:55.848
I should've gotten adopted
by madonna.

01:55.850 --> 01:57.716
I should've peed at home.

01:59.285 --> 02:00.886
I think they're using
a different brand of hot dog.

02:00.888 --> 02:03.422
I didn't hear the snap.

02:03.424 --> 02:05.557
Did you hear the snap?

02:05.559 --> 02:08.560
I hear
my social status crashing.

02:08.562 --> 02:10.562
There it goes.

02:10.564 --> 02:13.732
<i>Now batting number 9,</i>
<i>jack johnson.</i>

02:13.734 --> 02:16.435
<i>Let's see</i>
<i>what this natural athlete</i>

02:16.437 --> 02:18.804
<i>Can do against</i>
<i>this smart pitcher.</i>

02:18.806 --> 02:21.306
What does that mean?

02:21.308 --> 02:24.910
This announcer --
I don't like what he's saying.

02:24.912 --> 02:27.846
Run! Run!

02:27.848 --> 02:30.849
<i>No chance for a play,</i>
<i>not the way this boy runs --</i>

02:30.851 --> 02:32.918
<i>Like a panther.</i>

02:32.920 --> 02:36.255
Oh, come on.

02:36.257 --> 02:39.291
Ladies, that doesn't strike
any of you as odd?

02:39.293 --> 02:41.793
Natural athlete?
Panther?

02:41.795 --> 02:43.762
That's
pretty coded language.

02:43.764 --> 02:45.864
Didn't pick that up.
No?
No.

02:45.866 --> 02:48.333
[ chuckles ] it's okay.
My husband will understand.

02:48.335 --> 02:49.535
Dre.
Hmm?

02:49.537 --> 02:50.936
Dre, come here.
I want to talk to you.

02:50.938 --> 02:52.337
Nice hit, jack!
Way to go!

02:52.339 --> 02:53.572
My genes.
Yeah.

02:53.574 --> 02:54.806
Dre.
What?

02:54.808 --> 02:56.575
Did you hear
that announcer?

02:56.577 --> 02:58.644
Not really.
I was listening to my hot dog.

02:58.646 --> 03:01.547
He said some weird stuff
about jack

03:01.549 --> 03:03.448
That really raised
my racial antenna.

03:03.450 --> 03:05.918
Oh. Really?

03:06.953 --> 03:08.520
Your race card, sir.

03:08.522 --> 03:11.790
Ah, my african-american
express.

03:11.792 --> 03:14.760
I've been waiting
since yesterday to use you.

03:14.762 --> 03:16.195
Hit me with it.
What did I miss?

03:16.197 --> 03:17.529
Okay, well, he started

03:17.531 --> 03:20.465
By saying jack
was a natural athlete.
Which he is.

03:20.467 --> 03:21.934
And then he called
the other kids smart,

03:21.936 --> 03:23.435
But he didn't call
jack smart.

03:23.437 --> 03:24.937
Well --

03:24.939 --> 03:26.939
Dre, and then he said our baby
ran like a panther.

03:26.941 --> 03:28.273
That's cool.
Come on.

03:28.275 --> 03:29.908
Get to the juicy
offensive stuff.

03:29.910 --> 03:31.977
I got this race card
burning a hole in my pocket.

03:31.979 --> 03:34.780
<i>Look at him go!</i>

03:34.782 --> 03:37.416
<i>This kid was born to steal!</i>

03:37.418 --> 03:38.750
[ laughs ]
see?!

03:38.752 --> 03:40.252
What?
[ stammers ]

03:40.254 --> 03:41.687
That is exactly what
I'm talking about.

03:41.689 --> 03:47.326
Bow, he said jack was born
to steal bases, not tvs.

03:47.328 --> 03:50.362
Sadly, I won't be playing
my race card today.

03:50.364 --> 03:52.364
Very good, sir.

03:52.366 --> 03:54.967
Will I be seeing you later
at chick-fil-a?

03:54.969 --> 03:56.802
Probably.

03:56.804 --> 03:58.303
Why are you
just standing there?

03:58.305 --> 04:00.005
Because you're not gonna have me
going around here

04:00.007 --> 04:01.640
Playing the race card
all willy-nilly.

04:01.642 --> 04:03.675
I'm not donald trump.
Are you serious?

04:03.677 --> 04:05.677
Bow, I think this is
more of a sports thing

04:05.679 --> 04:07.346
And not a race thing.

04:07.348 --> 04:08.680
We think so, too.

04:08.682 --> 04:09.715
Hey.

04:09.717 --> 04:11.817
Thank you. Okay.

04:11.819 --> 04:15.654
Dre, you're the marco polo
of racism.

04:15.656 --> 04:17.689
You find racism
everywhere.

04:17.691 --> 04:20.726
Because racism<i> is</i> everywhere,
except here.

04:20.728 --> 04:21.760
Okay.

04:21.762 --> 04:22.928
Hey, jack!

04:22.930 --> 04:24.596
Run like the cops
is on yo ass!

04:24.598 --> 04:27.299
[ laughs ] whoo!

04:27.301 --> 04:29.835
So, that was fun, huh?
Rainbow: Which part?

04:29.837 --> 04:31.503
The part where you
threw me under the bus

04:31.505 --> 04:32.938
Or the part
where you stepped on the gas?

04:32.940 --> 04:35.407
What?
You had me looking
like a jackass, dre.

04:35.409 --> 04:37.309
You just left me
flapping in the wind

04:37.311 --> 04:38.510
All flippity flip flap.

04:38.512 --> 04:39.945
I thought we were
team johnson.

04:39.947 --> 04:41.413
We are, babe, but --

04:41.415 --> 04:43.415
All those moms looking at me
like I was a nut.

04:43.417 --> 04:44.983
Well, there were
some dads, too.

04:44.985 --> 04:46.418
[ sighs ]

04:46.420 --> 04:48.287
Why do I blurt?

04:48.289 --> 04:49.788
Even if you thought
I was wrong,

04:49.790 --> 04:52.858
Which I was not,
you should've had my back.

04:52.860 --> 04:55.027
Okay, so, you want me
to act like you're right

04:55.029 --> 04:56.995
Even when you're wrong?
Precisely.

04:56.997 --> 04:58.397
And agree with you
when I don't.

04:58.399 --> 05:00.465
Yes.
That would be best.

05:00.467 --> 05:01.933
Ah.

05:01.935 --> 05:03.802
Okay.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.772
So, you threw your wife
under the bus, dre?

05:06.774 --> 05:08.307
That's a bad move.

05:08.309 --> 05:09.975
I did the same thing
to margaret.

05:09.977 --> 05:12.344
Broke up our first
and third marriages.

05:12.346 --> 05:15.647
She was much nicer
to me the third time.

05:15.649 --> 05:16.782
Well, not to me.

05:16.784 --> 05:18.350
Look, whatever
your differences are,

05:18.352 --> 05:21.086
Figure it out, because we need
all spouses here tonight

05:21.088 --> 05:22.087
For the museum event.

05:22.089 --> 05:23.388
It's a huge new client.

05:23.390 --> 05:24.890
Damn it!
I forgot about that.

05:24.892 --> 05:27.859
Hopefully, I can convince bow
to go with me.

05:27.861 --> 05:29.861
We need bow here tonight,
okay?

05:29.863 --> 05:31.330
She knows all about art,

05:31.332 --> 05:33.632
And my wife knows
nothing about nothing.

05:33.634 --> 05:34.900
That's what you get

05:34.902 --> 05:38.036
When you make small talk
on a southwest flight.

05:39.539 --> 05:44.009
So, you spent all of yesterday
making me look bad,

05:44.011 --> 05:47.112
And I'm supposed to spend
tonight making you look good?

05:47.114 --> 05:49.715
Yes, that's what I'm asking.
Mm-hmm.

05:49.717 --> 05:51.483
Plus, you look so sexy
when you talk art.

05:51.485 --> 05:52.984
Dre.
Hey, mama.

05:52.986 --> 05:54.820
Talk some art
for me right now, please.

05:54.822 --> 05:57.723
Come on, baby,
talk that art to me.
Stop.

05:57.725 --> 06:01.126
You mean like...Cezanne?

06:01.128 --> 06:02.894
What about cezanne?

06:02.896 --> 06:06.498
Well, he was known
for his very tight brush work.

06:06.500 --> 06:09.735
[ bowl slams ]
damn it, you know I love
tight brush work.

06:09.737 --> 06:13.505
He would fill an entire canvas
with his landscape.

06:13.507 --> 06:14.773
[ pops lips ]

06:14.775 --> 06:15.841
[ pops lips ]

06:15.843 --> 06:17.776
[ chuckles ]
don't stop. Don't stop.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.811
He loved to experiment.
[ breathing heavily ] with what?

06:19.813 --> 06:22.547
Muted colors.
Ooh!

06:22.549 --> 06:23.782
Stop it.
Okay, okay.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.050
Save some for the party.

06:25.052 --> 06:26.818
Fine, but you need to tell
zoey and junior

06:26.820 --> 06:27.886
That they're babysitting
tonight.

06:27.888 --> 06:29.454
Babysit?!

06:29.456 --> 06:30.822
But mom said zach and I

06:30.824 --> 06:33.558
Could wear costumes
to the new marvel movie.

06:33.560 --> 06:35.727
Yeah, I may not have thought
that one through.

06:35.729 --> 06:36.995
Trust me, son,
I'm doing you a favor

06:36.997 --> 06:38.397
By not letting you
do that.

06:38.399 --> 06:39.931
So, we're stuck sitting?

06:39.933 --> 06:42.434
Look, man, sitting is something
you excel at.

06:42.436 --> 06:44.169
This is so not fair.

06:44.171 --> 06:46.938
Not only is it fair,
it's by design.

06:46.940 --> 06:48.607
Your mother and I
waited eight years

06:48.609 --> 06:50.709
After you were born
before having more children

06:50.711 --> 06:52.844
So we could take advantage
of moments like this.

06:52.846 --> 06:55.180
That's what I call
planned parenthood.
Up top.

06:55.182 --> 06:56.748
Yep.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.951
[ up-tempo music plays ]

07:02.955 --> 07:07.526
Dre:<i> So, I was glad I dragged</i>
<i>my wife out from under the bus.</i>

07:07.528 --> 07:08.860
<i>She was doing great.</i>

07:08.862 --> 07:12.164
Caravaggio's use
of chiaroscuro is beautiful.

07:12.166 --> 07:16.535
Unlike a master barista's
use of cappuccino,

07:16.537 --> 07:18.637
Which is delicious.

07:18.639 --> 07:20.939
[ laughter ]

07:20.941 --> 07:22.974
Coffee makes me poop.

07:22.976 --> 07:24.142
Oh.
Mm.

07:24.144 --> 07:25.911
Okay.
Okeydoke.

07:25.913 --> 07:26.978
All righty.
Okay.

07:26.980 --> 07:29.114
My god.
What have I done?

07:29.116 --> 07:31.116
[ both laugh ]

07:31.118 --> 07:32.951
She's not wrong,
though.
I know.

07:32.953 --> 07:35.854
Don't say anything
'cause she's my best friend,

07:35.856 --> 07:38.190
But she totally talks
behind people's backs.

07:38.192 --> 07:39.991
[ clears throat ]

07:39.993 --> 07:42.461
I want some chunky monkey.
I need it.

07:42.463 --> 07:43.962
I'm bored.

07:43.964 --> 07:46.965
I want
to be entertained.

07:46.967 --> 07:49.134
Oh, then why don't we
play a game?

07:49.136 --> 07:51.503
Follow me.

07:51.505 --> 07:54.105
Stand right there.

07:54.107 --> 07:56.775
Close your eyes.
[ both gasp ]

07:58.644 --> 08:00.679
I'm gonna be an awesome mom.

08:00.681 --> 08:03.515
She should not have
children.

08:03.517 --> 08:05.851
Hey, junior, can we play --
[ music plays
through headphones ]

08:05.853 --> 08:09.688
Guess we have to entertain
ourselves.

08:09.690 --> 08:11.022
[ dramatic music plays ]

08:11.024 --> 08:13.825
You thinking
what I'm thinking?

08:13.827 --> 08:15.494
[ both laughing, screaming ]

08:17.864 --> 08:19.130
Junior:
Okay. Here we go.

08:19.132 --> 08:20.966
Are you crazy?

08:20.968 --> 08:23.502
You can't let them ride
down the stairs like that.

08:23.504 --> 08:26.571
They need helmets.

08:26.573 --> 08:29.074
Both: Whoo!

08:32.011 --> 08:33.879
Okay, let's get
one thing straight --

08:33.881 --> 08:36.615
None of this
was my fault.

08:37.149 --> 08:38.950
Man: Dre you've been
to the museum

08:38.952 --> 08:40.619
Since we opened up
the new wing, right?

08:40.621 --> 08:42.621
What? I practically live
in that wing.

08:42.623 --> 08:44.256
[ chuckles ]
I love wings.

08:44.258 --> 08:45.624
You'll have to come down

08:45.626 --> 08:47.726
When we open
our retrospective on matisse.

08:47.728 --> 08:48.994
Try and stop me.

08:48.996 --> 08:51.930
There are two things I love --
wings and matisse.

08:51.932 --> 08:53.565
Rainbow: Oh. [ laughs ]

08:53.567 --> 08:54.933
I couldn't help but to overhear

08:54.935 --> 08:56.701
You guys are talking about
one of my favorite artists.

08:56.703 --> 08:58.203
He's wonderful.

08:58.205 --> 09:00.906
I recently dragged dre
to one of his exhibits,

09:00.908 --> 09:02.941
And even he got it.

09:02.943 --> 09:04.843
I did.
What?

09:04.845 --> 09:06.978
<i>I don't remember going</i>
<i>to see matisse.</i>

09:06.980 --> 09:10.315
<i>I tend to remember doing things</i>
<i>I hate, but she's the expert.</i>

09:10.317 --> 09:14.286
I think that he is one
of the greatest surrealists.

09:14.288 --> 09:17.055
I do, and this idea
that what is real

09:17.057 --> 09:20.125
Lies right behind
what you actually see.

09:20.127 --> 09:23.895
I mean, that's mind blowing,
to me.

09:23.897 --> 09:25.697
<i>Why are they looking at her</i>

09:25.699 --> 09:28.099
<i>Like she has a big, old booger</i>
<i>in her nose?</i>

09:32.605 --> 09:34.139
<i>Let me google this real quick.</i>

09:34.141 --> 09:37.609
<i>We did go see some artist</i>
<i>that started with an "m."</i>

09:37.611 --> 09:39.878
<i>M-a, m-a, m-- ooh!</i>

09:39.880 --> 09:42.914
<i>Match ups for the new college</i>
<i>football playoff system.</i>

09:42.916 --> 09:43.915
<i>That's cool.</i>

09:43.917 --> 09:45.784
<i>Damn it, dre, stay on track.</i>

09:45.786 --> 09:47.619
I actually get uneasy

09:47.621 --> 09:50.221
When I see a man in a suit
with a bowler hat

09:50.223 --> 09:53.625
And there isn't a giant piece
of fruit obscuring his face.

09:53.627 --> 09:55.660
<i>Bowler hat -- magritte.</i>

09:55.662 --> 09:57.596
<i>She's talking about magritte.</i>

09:57.598 --> 09:58.630
<i>Wrong guy.</i>

09:58.632 --> 09:59.798
<i>I'm gonna tell her.</i>

09:59.800 --> 10:03.168
<i>She said not to disagree</i>
<i>with her in public,</i>

10:03.170 --> 10:05.070
<i>But this is different, right?</i>
Babe.

10:05.072 --> 10:06.738
Ciao. Ciao.

10:06.740 --> 10:07.939
I hope we get to talk more.

10:07.941 --> 10:09.975
Hey, babe.
Yeah. Hey, killing it.

10:09.977 --> 10:11.309
Okay. Hang on.
I love it.

10:11.311 --> 10:13.812
Ooh! I love art!

10:13.814 --> 10:15.313
[ groans ]

10:15.315 --> 10:17.315
That was amazing.

10:17.317 --> 10:20.785
I was on fire.

10:20.787 --> 10:24.389
I don't think anybody even
noticed that matisse thing.

10:24.391 --> 10:26.825
The what?
Uh, the matisse thing.

10:26.827 --> 10:28.860
You know, everybody was
talking matisse, but you
were talking magritte.

10:28.862 --> 10:31.162
Wait,
are you -- d-- no.

10:31.164 --> 10:32.864
What?!
Uh-huh.

10:32.866 --> 10:34.332
Dre, get off the phone.

10:34.334 --> 10:37.035
Hey, I did not interrupt
or contradict you.

10:37.037 --> 10:38.069
You're welcome.

10:38.071 --> 10:39.938
<i>You killed it, dre.</i>

10:39.940 --> 10:42.841
You had time to google it,
and you didn't tell me?

10:42.843 --> 10:45.977
Dre, I referenced magritte
like 10 times.
I know!

10:45.979 --> 10:48.113
You know a lot
about magritte.

10:48.115 --> 10:49.981
Are you trying
to make me stab you?

10:49.983 --> 10:52.651
Dre, I can't belive you did
that to me again.

10:52.653 --> 10:54.953
Are you saying
I threw you under the bus

10:54.955 --> 10:56.154
By not throwing you
under the bus?

10:56.156 --> 10:57.689
Yes!
What?

11:00.126 --> 11:01.993
I don't understand
the rules.

11:04.930 --> 11:08.033
Okay, we've got one shot
to get this right.

11:08.035 --> 11:10.068
Mom and dad can never know
what happened.

11:10.070 --> 11:11.236
Okay, team johnson.

11:11.238 --> 11:12.937
[ all shout indistinctly ]

11:12.939 --> 11:14.072
[ sighs ] go.
Just go.

11:14.074 --> 11:17.042
Junior: Look pathetic!
[ door opens ]

11:17.044 --> 11:19.377
Oh, my god.
What --

11:19.379 --> 11:20.679
What happened?

11:20.681 --> 11:22.113
We had a little snafu.

11:22.115 --> 11:25.350
Is that diane is conscious
and breathing on her own.

11:25.352 --> 11:28.353
Oh, my god!
Baby, are you okay?

11:28.355 --> 11:30.955
[ groans ]
what happened?

11:30.957 --> 11:33.892
Well, after we all ate a bunch
of broccoli -- steamed --

11:33.894 --> 11:35.860
We were looking
for family fun activities.

11:35.862 --> 11:37.962
Yeah, something
that would help us bond

11:37.964 --> 11:39.698
With our younger siblings.

11:39.700 --> 11:41.866
So, we decided
to play project runway, and...

11:41.868 --> 11:45.904
I was modeling the shoes
you promise I'll grow into,

11:45.906 --> 11:48.039
And then
I fell down the stairs.
Oh, my god.

11:48.041 --> 11:50.875
Classic slip and fall,
but she's not gonna sue.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.877
[ groans ]

11:52.879 --> 11:55.747
I don't think.
Oh, my god.

11:55.749 --> 11:57.415
Sweetheart, I'm so sorry.

11:57.417 --> 11:59.250
This was all my fault.

11:59.252 --> 12:00.685
I should've
never bought you

12:00.687 --> 12:02.320
Those big shoes
for your teeny, little feet.

12:02.322 --> 12:03.988
<i>Things weren't adding up,</i>

12:03.990 --> 12:06.858
<i>And bow</i>
<i>was feeling pretty guilty.</i>

12:06.860 --> 12:09.094
<i>I figured if I could</i>
<i>find out the truth,</i>

12:09.096 --> 12:11.830
<i>I could give bow</i>
<i>a clear conscience,</i>

12:11.832 --> 12:15.033
<i>And she could give me a break</i>
<i>for my matisse screw-up.</i>

12:15.035 --> 12:18.937
<i>So I set out</i>
<i>to investigate "csi" style.</i>

12:19.939 --> 12:22.040
♪ flash light ♪

12:24.276 --> 12:26.811
♪ flash light ♪

12:26.813 --> 12:28.980
Oh...

12:28.982 --> 12:31.082
♪ flash light ♪

12:33.419 --> 12:35.386
♪ flash light ♪

12:38.357 --> 12:42.527
♪ ha, da, da, dee, da,
hada, hada, da, da ♪

12:43.996 --> 12:47.832
<i>It was time to shake some trees</i>
<i>and see what falls out.</i>

12:48.968 --> 12:51.002
Hey!
Weak link, wake up.

12:51.004 --> 12:52.437
Is this the big one?

12:52.439 --> 12:54.372
Okay, I've got an earthquake kit
under the bed.

12:54.374 --> 12:55.940
