in the closet.

12:55.942 --> 12:57.976
I've got traveler's checks
in my money belt.

12:57.978 --> 13:00.011
Let's go!
Hey, hey, hey,
sit down.

13:00.013 --> 13:02.046
How did the hole
get in the wall?

13:04.283 --> 13:07.018
Just like
we told you, dad.

13:10.289 --> 13:12.991
[ cellphone chimes ]

13:12.993 --> 13:14.359
Junior just gave you up,

13:14.361 --> 13:16.327
So you might as well
confess now.

13:16.329 --> 13:18.563
If he gave us up,
why are you here?

13:21.066 --> 13:23.067
Why are<i> you</i> here?

13:23.069 --> 13:24.536
It's my room.
Oh.

13:24.538 --> 13:26.504
Why don't you go holler
at your wife?

13:26.506 --> 13:29.574
She's the one who bought
those mary jane death traps.

13:29.576 --> 13:31.142
How --

13:31.144 --> 13:33.578
She almost killed diane.

13:33.580 --> 13:34.913
I'm sorry.

13:38.417 --> 13:41.486
I'm watching you.

13:41.488 --> 13:44.022
Mm-hmm.

13:44.024 --> 13:45.557
Mm-hmm.

13:45.559 --> 13:48.193
Mm-hmm.

13:51.030 --> 13:52.530
Okay.

13:52.532 --> 13:56.067
Now that I'm satisfied
your story holds up,

13:56.069 --> 13:59.504
I'm gonna reward myself
with some chunky monkey.

14:01.106 --> 14:02.507
Good night.

14:09.950 --> 14:15.854
You know, I totally forgot
that you love chunky monkey.

14:15.856 --> 14:18.556
Would you like some?
Yes, I would.

14:18.558 --> 14:20.124
I'm sure you would.

14:20.126 --> 14:21.926
You know what goes
really good with chunky monkey?

14:21.928 --> 14:23.928
What?
[ laughs ]

14:23.930 --> 14:26.431
Whipped cream.
Mmm.

14:26.433 --> 14:28.066
Mmm!

14:28.068 --> 14:30.368
And the truth.
[ sighs ]

14:30.370 --> 14:33.137
Okay, okay,
I'll tell you everything.

14:33.139 --> 14:35.907
Zoey and junior
totally abandoned us,

14:35.909 --> 14:38.910
Then jack threw me in a basket,
then pushed me down the stairs.

14:38.912 --> 14:40.945
Hmm?
More whipped cream, please.

14:40.947 --> 14:42.113
[ chuckles ]

14:45.084 --> 14:47.051
Use a spoon.
Mnh-mnh.

14:47.053 --> 14:49.420
<i>So, I told bow</i>
<i>what really happened,</i>

14:49.422 --> 14:51.289
<i>And I knew</i>
<i>she'd let me off the hook.</i>

14:51.291 --> 14:53.324
So you can stop
feeling guilty now.

14:53.326 --> 14:54.959
Gee. Thanks.

14:54.961 --> 14:57.929
It wasn't easy
getting this info from the kids.

14:57.931 --> 14:59.664
They closed ranks.

14:59.666 --> 15:01.933
Oh, so they had
each other's backs, huh?

15:01.935 --> 15:03.334
They were team johnson.

15:03.336 --> 15:04.535
Babe, you know what?
Huh?

15:04.537 --> 15:06.170
We can learn something
from the kids.

15:06.172 --> 15:08.673
No,<i> you</i> could
learn something.

15:08.675 --> 15:10.575
I'm good.
I --

15:10.577 --> 15:12.277
[ door closes ]

15:12.279 --> 15:16.481
<i>My peace offering to bow</i>
<i>had gone unappreciated.</i>

15:16.483 --> 15:19.651
<i>Time for my next strategy --</i>
<i>a common enemy.</i>

15:19.653 --> 15:22.120
<i>And I knew just the one.</i>

15:23.289 --> 15:25.056
Foul ball!

15:25.058 --> 15:26.190
Foul ball?!

15:26.192 --> 15:27.392
You know, this is it.

15:27.394 --> 15:29.127
I've had enough
of this guy.

15:29.129 --> 15:30.461
Dre, he didn't say
anything.

15:30.463 --> 15:31.930
What?
You didn't hear it?

15:31.932 --> 15:33.031
It was outrageous.

15:33.033 --> 15:35.300
Outrageous!

15:35.302 --> 15:36.401
So...You guys
want a blow pop?

15:36.403 --> 15:38.670
Not from you, snitch.

15:38.672 --> 15:40.338
You went
against the family.

15:40.340 --> 15:42.540
Your candy is dead
to us.

15:42.542 --> 15:44.676
[ smooches ]

15:44.678 --> 15:46.177
You broke my heart.

15:46.179 --> 15:49.180
And another foul ball.

15:49.182 --> 15:52.483
You and your foul balls.

15:52.485 --> 15:54.719
You know what's foul?
Everything you say.

15:54.721 --> 15:56.554
Huh?
The things that you say.

15:56.556 --> 16:00.091
<i>Natural athlete,</i>
<i>born to steal, foul balls.</i>

16:00.093 --> 16:02.060
<i>It's offensive,</i>
<i>all right?</i>

16:02.062 --> 16:04.529
You've got my wife,
dr. Rainbow johnson,

16:04.531 --> 16:06.731
<i>All worked up,</i>
<i>and she should be.</i>

16:06.733 --> 16:08.733
<i>She could not be</i>
<i>more right</i>

16:08.735 --> 16:10.535
<i>About the offensive</i>
<i>and inappropriate things</i>

16:10.537 --> 16:11.703
<i>You say</i>
<i>about those children.</i>

16:11.705 --> 16:13.171
<i>I'm surprised</i>
<i>one of these kids</i>

16:13.173 --> 16:15.106
<i>Ain't come up here</i>
<i>and kicked your ass.</i>

16:15.108 --> 16:16.240
[ crowd murmuring ]

16:18.110 --> 16:21.079
I really don't know
what you're talking about.

16:21.081 --> 16:22.413
Of course you don't.

16:22.415 --> 16:24.449
Ignorant people never do.

16:24.451 --> 16:27.118
So, I'm shutting you down
right now.

16:28.153 --> 16:30.154
[ laughs ]
I'm sorry.

16:30.156 --> 16:32.090
I didn't mean none of that stuff
I just said.

16:32.092 --> 16:34.192
I had to make it
at least appear

16:34.194 --> 16:35.693
That I was setting you straight
for my wife.

16:35.695 --> 16:37.695
You know, she can be
a little cuckoo sometimes.

16:37.697 --> 16:40.098
You understand, right?
I do.

16:40.100 --> 16:41.733
But what
I don't understand

16:41.735 --> 16:44.035
Is why you turned off
the scoreboard.

16:44.037 --> 16:46.404
No, no, no,
I turned off the microphone.

16:46.406 --> 16:47.438
No.

16:47.440 --> 16:49.207
<i>Scoreboard.</i>

16:53.779 --> 16:55.079
Hmm?

16:56.615 --> 16:58.416
Uh...

16:58.418 --> 17:01.152
Batting seventh,

17:01.154 --> 17:04.489
<i>Aiden schulman.</i>

17:04.491 --> 17:07.258
[ beeps ]

17:07.260 --> 17:09.127
It's cool.

17:12.798 --> 17:15.700
<i>The plan to keep</i>
<i>team johnson together</i>

17:15.702 --> 17:18.036
<i>Had pretty much been reduced</i>
<i>to ashes.</i>

17:18.038 --> 17:21.372
<i>The kids were mad at each</i>
<i>other, and bow was mad at me.</i>

17:21.374 --> 17:23.307
Hey. Can we talk?

17:24.343 --> 17:26.044
Uh, that's okay.

17:26.046 --> 17:28.379
I pretty much know
what you would say.
Really?

17:28.381 --> 17:29.647
'cause there's a lot
of profanity

17:29.649 --> 17:31.349
Just behind my eyes.

17:31.351 --> 17:33.718
Mm-hmm.
Maybe after dinner.

17:33.720 --> 17:34.819
[ scoffs ]

17:34.821 --> 17:36.821
Eh.

17:36.823 --> 17:39.524
I'm gonna eat later.

17:40.559 --> 17:41.826
I'm gonna eat in my room.

17:41.828 --> 17:44.128
I don't want to eat alone
with the snitch.

17:44.130 --> 17:45.430
I'm going outside.

17:45.432 --> 17:47.365
Dre: Hey!
Hey, that's enough!

17:47.367 --> 17:49.767
Family meeting, living room,
now!

17:51.837 --> 17:53.704
Really?

17:53.706 --> 17:55.139
Just me and you?

17:55.141 --> 17:56.374
This is ridiculous.

17:56.376 --> 17:57.842
I don't disagree.

17:57.844 --> 18:01.512
Maybe they don't respect you
like I do.

18:01.514 --> 18:02.713
I guess not.

18:02.715 --> 18:04.715
Seems like
the only thing left to do

18:04.717 --> 18:06.784
Is have some ice cream.

18:06.786 --> 18:08.786
[ doorbell rings ]

18:08.788 --> 18:10.354
Hold on
to that thought.

18:12.524 --> 18:13.825
Ah.

18:13.827 --> 18:15.860
Hey, what's going on?
Hey, dre.

18:15.862 --> 18:18.162
Sorry to bother you at home,
but I thought it was better

18:18.164 --> 18:20.565
Than sending out one
of those crappy team e-mails.

18:20.567 --> 18:23.101
Cool.
I don't read those, anyway.
No one does.

18:23.103 --> 18:24.702
I take a lot of time
to craft my e-mails.

18:24.704 --> 18:27.772
We're here about
the loudspeaker incident.

18:27.774 --> 18:30.141
It was an incident?
Yeah.

18:30.143 --> 18:32.143
Yeah, we have some
very upset parents.

18:32.145 --> 18:35.446
It's the worst behavior
the league has ever seen.

18:35.448 --> 18:37.148
[ scoffs ]
worse than
that old streaker

18:37.150 --> 18:38.883
That wandered into the middle
of a tee-ball game?

18:38.885 --> 18:41.452
Jeremy's grandfather
has dementia.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.788
Uh...Okay.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.690
So, we're gonna have to ask you
to stay away

18:45.692 --> 18:49.560
What?
And we've asked jeremy's
grandfather to do the same.

18:49.562 --> 18:52.530
You're banning him
from the complex?

18:52.532 --> 18:56.901
He was naked in front
of children.

18:56.903 --> 18:58.136
No. My husband.

18:58.138 --> 18:59.804
Bow,
we got to do something.

18:59.806 --> 19:01.606
And I'm sure
even dre would admit

19:01.608 --> 19:03.774
That he acted
like an idiot.

19:03.776 --> 19:06.310
Would dre?
No, no,
dre would not,

19:06.312 --> 19:08.146
Because he
is not an idiot.

19:08.148 --> 19:09.547
People get carried away

19:09.549 --> 19:11.315
At that stupid field
all the time.

19:11.317 --> 19:13.317
This man cares about his family,
and he made a mistake.

19:13.319 --> 19:14.852
So, if you're gonna ban
a johnson,

19:14.854 --> 19:18.456
You're banning all of us,
and that includes jack, yeah.

19:18.458 --> 19:20.191
And you know that boy
runs like a panther.

19:20.193 --> 19:22.160
Yes.
Very fleet footed.

19:22.162 --> 19:23.794
Good night
to both of you.
Okay.

19:23.796 --> 19:25.530
Yes, good night.
Good night.
Yes.

19:25.532 --> 19:27.598
We will see you
in a couple of weeks.
Thank you.

19:27.600 --> 19:28.766
That's ridiculous.
Wow.

19:28.768 --> 19:31.936
Hey, babe,
did you really mean that?

19:31.938 --> 19:33.504
No. You're an idiot.
Oh.

19:33.506 --> 19:35.606
But I would never
tell them that.

19:35.608 --> 19:38.376
That is called
having someone's back.

19:38.378 --> 19:39.911
You're right,
and I'm sorry.

19:39.913 --> 19:42.847
But I wasn't kidding
when I said I didn't
understand your rules.

19:42.849 --> 19:44.315
They're really hard.

19:44.317 --> 19:46.484
Just show me
that you're there for me,

19:46.486 --> 19:49.220
And never let me
embarrass myself.

19:49.222 --> 19:50.354
Cool.

19:50.356 --> 19:52.456
But what about karaoke?

19:52.458 --> 19:54.358
What about karaoke?

19:54.360 --> 19:56.794
I really don't understand
these rules.

19:56.796 --> 19:58.963
What about karaoke?

19:58.965 --> 20:00.765
I -- okay.

20:00.767 --> 20:04.202
I mean...
I'm amazing at karaoke.

20:04.204 --> 20:06.871
See what mom
just did, diane?

20:06.873 --> 20:08.573
That's what loyalty
looks like.

20:08.575 --> 20:09.840
I'm sorry, okay?

20:09.842 --> 20:11.676
Daddy
had chunky monkey.

20:11.678 --> 20:13.377
I would've broken
for ice cream.

20:13.379 --> 20:14.845
I forgive you.

20:14.847 --> 20:18.683
Well, I guess you're only 7,
so I forgive you, too.

20:18.685 --> 20:20.451
What about you, junior?

20:20.453 --> 20:26.490
Dad gripped me up out of bed
and shined a light in my eyes.

20:26.492 --> 20:28.659
What?

20:28.661 --> 20:30.628
[ sighs ]

20:30.630 --> 20:33.264
<i>So, there were a few bumps</i>
<i>along the way,</i>

20:33.266 --> 20:36.601
<i>But in the end, team johnson</i>
<i>came together for the win.</i>

20:36.603 --> 20:38.836
<i>One way or another,</i>
<i>we had each other's backs.</i>

20:38.838 --> 20:40.905
<i>Little do they know,</i>

20:40.907 --> 20:43.808
<i>I'll be kicking their butts</i>
<i>in bananagrams later.</i>

20:46.511 --> 20:49.747
[ off-key ] ♪ we build it up and
build it up and build it up ♪

20:49.749 --> 20:52.583
♪ and 'cause it's solid ♪

20:52.585 --> 20:56.020
♪ solid as a rock ♪

20:56.022 --> 20:58.456
[ laughs ] yeah!
Yay, mommy!

20:58.458 --> 21:00.825
Mommy! Whoo!
Wonderful.

21:00.827 --> 21:02.927
Thank you so much.
You want me to do another one?

21:02.929 --> 21:04.929
Uh, do<i> you</i> want
to do another one?

21:04.931 --> 21:07.698
Only if<i> you</i> want me
to do another one.

21:07.700 --> 21:09.800
I want
what you want, baby.

21:09.802 --> 21:12.270
Okay, yes or no,
I'm embarrassing myself?

21:14.873 --> 21:17.875
I really, really don't
understand the rules.

